UML:TaggedValue.value: A formal carer is a professional carer who works for the community or a welfare organisation and gets paid for caring activities.
Contact with Formal Caregiver or Relative

An informal carer is a person who is not a professional carer or service provider. Informal carers are in most cases relatives (spouses, children) or friends of the assisted person. An informal carer normally does not receive any payment for caring for a relative or friends and can live in the same household as the assisted person or in a separate household.
